**Job Title**
 Senior Data Engineer EMEA (Kochi, India)




**Job Description Summary**
 Utilizing our state\\-of\\-the\\-art intelligent data platform, you will craft a specialized cloud solution designed for the real estate domain. This platform empowers every individual within Cushman \\& Wakefield to adeptly tackle location\\-based challenges, thereby guaranteeing improved client service and enabling well\\-informed, future\\-proof decision\\-making. Embrace the opportunity to leverage the expansive potential of our intelligent data platform and commence making a substantial impact in the real estate industry today!




**Job Description**
**About the Role:**
* Analyze, organize, and model complex datasets in preparation for data lineage and data ingestion;
* Design stable ETL solutions for datasets, matching business needs and technology trends;
* Build, implement, and optimize pipelines handling transactional, geospatial, and client data;
* Report on data quality and advise on potential improvements;
* Engage with diverse business stakeholders to develop tailored cloud solutions that meet their specific needs and objectives;


**Top 3 Responsibilities**
* Translate business requirements into solid ETL solutions;
* Establish stable automated data ingestion pipelines;
* Create data marts to enable data availability for various use cases;


**About You**
* You have a minimum of 4 years of experience with data engineering or data analysis;
* You have academic education and work level;
* You speak and write excellent English;
* You have knowledge of SQL, Python, and PySpark;
* You have experience with Azure Microsoft Fabric and Databricks;
* Ability to collaborate effectively in a cross\\-functional team environment;
* Engaged in Data Management tasks, including ensuring Data Governance and maintaining Data Observability;
* Experience working with big geospatial data (prefered);


**Why join Cushman \\& Wakefield?**
 As one of the leading global real estate services firms transforming the way people work, shop and live working at Cushman \\& Wakefield means you will benefit from;  Being part of a growing global company;  Career development and a promote from within culture;  An organization committed to Diversity and Inclusion




 We're committed to providing work\\-life balance for our people in an inclusive, rewarding environment. We achieve this by providing a flexible and agile work environment by focusing on technology and autonomy to help our people achieve their career ambitions. We focus on career progression and foster a promotion from within culture, leveraging global opportunities to ensure we retain our top talent. We encourage continuous learning and development opportunities to develop personal, professional and technical capabilities, and we reward with a comprehensive employee benefits program.




**We have a vision of the future, where people simply belong.**
 That's why we support and celebrate inclusive causes, not just on days of recognition throughout the year, but every day. We embrace diversity across race, color, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, gender identity or persons with disabilities or protected veteran status. We ensure DEI is part of our DNA as a global community \\- it means we go way beyond than just talking about it \\- we live it. If you want to live it too, join us.




